=Asset type: {{ $json.asset_type }}
Usage context: {{ $json.usage_context }}
Aspect ratio: {{ $json.aspect_ratio }}
Size: {{ $json.size }}
Base prompt: {{ $json.prompt }}

Enhance this into a single rich natural language paragraph optimised for Adobe Firefly.
Include in order:
1. Subject and environment description
2. Lighting (be specific — quality, direction, color temperature)
3. Composition (rule of thirds, flat-lay, close-up etc.)
4. Color palette (describe in words, reference Navy Blue and Gold where appropriate)
5. Style reference (architectural photography, luxury product photography etc.)
6. Avoidance language (what to exclude — security camera tropes, dark surveillance imagery, red recording indicators, generic stock photo aesthetic)

End the enhanced_prompt with this line exactly:
Brand: {{ $json.brand_name }} | Asset: {{ $json.asset_type }} | Usage: {{ $json.usage_context }}

parameters.text:
=You are generating SVG mockups of the corporate stationery for the brand{{ $json.brand_name }}


Using the full visual identity brief and stationery specifications described in the system message, generate two SVG mockups: a business card and an A4 letterhead preview.
The business card viewbox must be exactly 0 0 340 208.
The letterhead viewbox must be exactly 0 0 595 842.
List every hex colour value you applied and confirm the viewbox used for each mockup. Note any layout decisions you made in generation_notes.


{{ $json.agent3_brief_md }}

parameters.jsCode:
const prompt = $input.first().json.prompt;
const executionId = $input.first().json.guid;

const command = `claude --dangerously-skip-permissions -p "/firefly-generate prompt=\`"${prompt}\`"
execution_id=\`"${executionId}\`""`;

return [{ json: { command, executionId } }];
